# HTTP requests in IntelliJ

If you need to do an http request without exit Intellij you could use the `Test Restful Web Service` but there is
another powerful tool to do the same: 
  * Create a new *scratch* file ( ⌃+⇧+↩ ) 
  * Select `HTTP Request` type
  * Type an url
  * Press ⌥+↩ and voila! 

There are a lot of options with this kind of file: verbs, headers, body, history, ... 
check [http://vojtechruzicka.com/intellij-idea-tips-tricks-testing-restful-web-services/](http://vojtechruzicka.com/intellij-idea-tips-tricks-testing-restful-web-services/)
